1
00:00:00,040 --> 00:00:03,243
This church was built in 1857

2
00:00:03,660 --> 00:00:08,920
This church was originally a plot of land purchased by two families

3
00:00:08,945 --> 00:00:13,321
One was the Syriac Orthodox Sarsami family, a well-known clan

4
00:00:13,816 --> 00:00:16,576
The other was the Armenian Chakmakjian family

5
00:00:16,941 --> 00:00:18,946
They partnered to buy the land

6
00:00:19,207 --> 00:00:22,853
And it was built in 1857

7
00:00:23,217 --> 00:00:28,321
Before that year, Armenians used to perform their prayers and rituals

8
00:00:28,346 --> 00:00:31,603
In the Citadel Church near this one

9
00:00:31,628 --> 00:00:34,233
The Tahira Inside Church of the Syriac Orthodox

10
00:00:34,701 --> 00:00:37,306
Which had been built earlier

11
00:00:37,331 --> 00:00:40,743
But after 1857

12
00:00:40,888 --> 00:00:44,508
The Armenians in Mosul had this church of their own

13
00:00:44,977 --> 00:00:46,747
And as is known

14
00:00:47,320 --> 00:00:51,304
The Armenians were subjected to many attacks

15
00:00:51,329 --> 00:00:55,784
Which led them to migrate from their areas of settlement in Turkey

16
00:00:56,018 --> 00:01:01,434
Their numbers reached thousands in Mosul in particular

17
00:01:01,459 --> 00:01:06,096
And they needed a church where they could hold their rituals
